&ldquo;Violence is not human destiny because the God of peace is the beginning and the end of human history&hellip;
&ldquo;Granted, pushing the stone of peace up the steep hill of violence &hellip; is hard. It is easier, however, than carrying one&rsquo;s own cross in the footsteps of the crucified Messiah. This is what Jesus Christ asks Christians to do. Assured of God&rsquo;s justice and undergirded by God&rsquo;s presence, they are to break the cycle of violence by refusing to be caught in the automatism of revenge.
